## OpenSpec-first Orchestration (C3 and C4 Implementation)

OpenSpec is the governance backbone for `C3` and `C4` implementation.

### Execution Gate (mandatory)

- Suggest only the next single `/opsx-*` (or `openspec ...`) step.
- Ask explicit yes/no before executing.
- Never auto-chain steps, especially archive.
- Never infer consent for `openspec archive <change-name> --yes`.

---

## Workflow Routing

### Routing model

- `C1`: advisory-only, no file edits.
- `C2`: direct deterministic small-change path.
- `C3`: OpenSpec-governed medium change.
- `C4`: mandatory Spec-Kit gate for discovery, then OpenSpec-governed implementation.

### C3 vs C4 route split (explicit)

| Category | Entry gate | Implementation starts when | Next lifecycle |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `C3` | `C3 Mandatory OpenSpec Gate` | OpenSpec change initialized | OpenSpec lifecycle |
| `C4` | `C4 Mandatory Spec-Kit Gate (Balanced)` | `Spec-Kit Gate: passed` | Spec-Kit discovery, then OpenSpec lifecycle |

### OpenSpec path (C3 and C4 implementation)

- Prefer `/opsx-*` wrappers when available.
- If wrappers are missing/outdated, run `openspec update` (Codex prompts are global: `~/.codex/prompts/`).
- If the repo is not OpenSpec-initialized, run `openspec init` at repo root.

> **Cross-tool syntax note:** Claude Code uses colon form (`/opsx:*`). Codex/OpenCode use hyphen form (`/opsx-*`).

Reference lifecycle:
- Start: `/opsx-new <change-name>`
- Plan artifacts: `/opsx-ff` (or `/opsx-continue`)
- Implement: `/opsx-apply`
- Verify: `/opsx-verify`
- Archive: `/opsx-archive` (explicit yes/no gate)

### Spec-Kit path (C4)

Initialize project-local command surface in target project:

```bash
specify init --here --ai codex --script sh
```

Gate behavior is defined in `Governed Workflow Gates (C3/C4)` above.

Cross-tool equivalents:

```bash
specify init --here --ai claude --script sh
specify init --here --ai opencode --script sh
```

If Codex project prompt discovery is missing after init, use:

```bash
export CODEX_HOME="$PWD/.codex"
```

### OpenSpec integration expectations (Codex)

OpenSpec integrations are generated by `openspec init/update`.

- OpenSpec workspace (project-local):
  - `openspec/specs/`, `openspec/changes/`, `openspec/changes/archive/`
  - Optional: `openspec/config.yaml` (never overwritten if already exists)

- Codex tool integration outputs:
  - Project skills: `./.codex/skills/<openspec-skill>/SKILL.md`
  - Global prompts (slash commands): `~/.codex/prompts/opsx-<id>.md` (or `$CODEX_HOME/prompts/…`)

> Note: Codex prompts are global by OpenSpec design. Running `openspec init/update` may modify `~/.codex/prompts/`.

### Version control note (gitignore)

This repository tracks all OpenSpec artifacts in git (`openspec/**`).
Active change directories under `openspec/changes/` must be archived before merge; CI enforces this via `.github/scripts/check_openspec_trace_gate.sh`.

